                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13911098" author="jmspaggi" created="Tue, 25 Feb 2014 01:39:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is there any real value to remove it? There is some useful methods like rollingSplit in it. And I don&apos;t think it&apos;s causing any issue to keep it, no?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13911138" author="ndimiduk" created="Tue, 25 Feb 2014 02:17:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I corrected the title after creating the issue. My intent is to remove the main() method, not the class itself. These useful methods and the split policy definitions are used by the shell, so let&apos;s keep those.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13913141" author="jmspaggi" created="Wed, 26 Feb 2014 16:52:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you remove the main, can you please make sure it&apos;s documented somewhere how to achieve the same thing with the shell, in case someone is still using it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13915638" author="anoop.hbase" created="Fri, 28 Feb 2014 10:21:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes Shell uses this. &lt;br/&gt;
Ideally Shell should work with out hbase server side jars&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/help_16.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;  This class is in hbase-server package.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13964631" author="phobos182" created="Wed, 9 Apr 2014 20:28:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FWIW we currently use the org.apache.hadoop.hbase.util.RegionSplitter with online rolling splits to perform capacity planning on live clusters. The HBase shell only allows for Splits for newly created tables I believe. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13964760" author="ndimiduk" created="Wed, 9 Apr 2014 22:45:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=phobos182&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;phobos182&quot;&gt;Jeremy Carroll&lt;/a&gt; fascinating. Would you be willing to contribute a section on the tool&apos;s use to the community &lt;a href=&quot;http://hbase.apache.org/book.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;book&lt;/a&gt;? You bring the content, I&apos;ll juggle the xml nonsense; deal?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Resolving as invalid.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14132028" author="phobos182" created="Fri, 12 Sep 2014 20:14:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Very late reply from myself. I can document the procedures we use internally. Where would I put this information?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14132063" author="stack" created="Fri, 12 Sep 2014 20:36:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=phobos182&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;phobos182&quot;&gt;Jeremy Carroll&lt;/a&gt; Stick a few lines here and if you are nice our mighty &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=misty&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;misty&quot;&gt;Misty Stanley-Jones&lt;/a&gt; will make a poem of them and stick it in refguide.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14331327" author="enis" created="Sat, 21 Feb 2015 23:35:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing this issue after 0.99.0 release. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
